<TITLE> Zillur, Bhuiyan want DU incident resolved through talks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com) -- Acting Awami League president Zillur Rahman and BNP secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan Tuesday urged the government to sit in a dialogue instead of using force to resolve the DU incident. They described the incident as sad. Zillur expressing his reaction to reporters at his Gulshan home Tuesday afternoon said: "We request the government to resolve the problem immediately by sitting with the students instead of using force." Zillur termed the incident "grievous and sad". "Many big problems can be solved through discussions," he said. He prayed for the early recovery of the students injured in the incident. In an instant reaction, Bhuiyan told bdnews24.com: "The incident at Dhaka University is very sad. I urge the government to take immediate steps to solve the problem peacefully to restore the academic environment of the university." Bhuiyan demanded proper treatment for those injured in the incident. bdnews24.
